node.text: Shared from @annmarisauctions (lovely items - well worth following!) A selection of lighting by Swedish designer Hans-Agne Jakobsson. After apprenticing as a carpenter Jakobsson studied architecture and, after working at General Motors, founded his own company in 1951 producing unique and imaginative works. #mcmdaily #hansagnejakobsson #nordicmodernism #sweden🇸🇪 mcmdaily.com

node.text: The Studebaker Avanti designed by  Tom Kellogg, Bob Andrews, and John Ebstein of Raymond Loewy’s design firm. Introduced at the 1962 New York International Auto Show the Avanti was conceived as a halo car to help bolster Studebaker‘a lagging sales. But despite favorable reviews the Avanti did not find a market and just under 6000 were sold during its one year production run. Photos: Mecum.com #mcmdaily #tomkellogg #bobandrews #johnebstein #raymondloewy #studebaker #studebakeravanti #classiccars #usa🇺🇸 mcmdaily.com

node.text: Located in the Rancho Palos Verdes suburb of Los Angeles, California the Rados House designed by architect Richard Neutra in 1957. node.text: Located in Espoo, Finland is the Haukilahti water tower. Designed by architect Erkko Virkkunen in 1968 the 151 ft / 46 m concrete structure is not only a municipale cistern the upper level is the Haikaranpesä restaurant and observation deck that provides a 360 degree view of the area. Photos: Risto Kamunen / Jussi Tiainen #mcmdaily #erkkovirkkunen #haukilahtiwatertower #finland🇫🇮 mcmdaily.com
